content: The Eiffel Tower can grow more than six inches in summer due to the expansion of the iron on hot days.
Australia is the only continent covered by a single country.
A group of flamingos is called a "flamboyance".
Bananas are berries while strawberries aren't.
The shortest war in history lasted 38-45 minutes between Britain and Zanzibar.
A day on Venus is longer than a year on Venus.
Almonds are members of the peach family.
The word "set" has the highest number of definitions in the English dictionary.

A cat has 32 muscles in each ear. The total weight of ants on earth once equaled the total weight of people. The heart of a shrimp is located in its head. The inventor of the Pringles can is now buried in one. Reindeers' eyes change color between summer and winter. Facebook is blue because Mark Zuckerberg is red-green colorblind. Barbie's full name is Barbara Millicent Roberts. The longest English word is 189,819 letters long. A hummingbird weighs less than a penny. The dot over an "i" or "j" is called a tittle. The Twitter bird's official name is Larry.
